{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Xu et al. [233] designed a parameter reduction technique aiming at the selection of financial ratios for the prediction of business failure.",
    "Kong et al. [151] argued that for large datasets, the previous algorithms were not computationally tractable.",
    "Consequently, they proposed that the particle swarm optimization algorithm could be more useful for parameter reduction of soft sets in this case.",
    "Other works that continue this trend include [204], who resort to the hybrid binary particle swarm and biogeography optimizer, and [189], whose metodology leans on the chi square distribution.",
    "For further reading about this topic, the reader can consult [88] and [246], who produced respective surveys of parameter reduction in the case of soft set theory."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Xu et al. [233] designed a parameter reduction technique aiming at the selection of financial ratios for the prediction of business failure.",
